examination of the external genital organs and perineum, in which the doctor
assesses the severity of edema of the glans penis, a change in its color (a
bluish tint is possible), the presence of pain and a “paraphimous ring” above
the coronal groove.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
